    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Located in the Rocky Mountain region and dubbed, the "Mile High City", Denver, CO is
a metropolitan city with a mild climate, and about 70 days of precipitation per year.
Containing over 200 parks, ranging from small to parks that that sit on thousands of acres,
there is much to do outside. With golf courses, swimming pools, trails, lakes and rivers,
there is an endless list of fun to be had! This might be why the city has gained a reputation
for being a very outdoor, active place. For those looking to be intellectually stimulated,
there are several museums, such as the Denver Museum of Nature and Science, and the
Denver Public Libraries. Other major attractions include the Denver Zoo and the Denver
Botanic Gardens. Known for its culture, there is an opera, symphony, art gallery, and
concert hall, all based locally. With many different shops and restaurants downtown, one
can spend hours wandering and not be bored. Those seeking sporting venues can visit a
number of places, including the Coors Field, the Pepsi Center and the Sports Authority Field
for baseball, football, and lacrosse teams. Come explore Denver and see what this mile high
city has to offer you!</p>
